<br>
We already do so little damage to those mobs (pulled for larger groups) that having an attack speed buff further lower our damage potential just seems evil.<br>
<br>
All of it seems evil.  I attack faster I want to do the same damage over time just lower the time without lowering the damage.  What the hell is the point of haste?  I don't see my strength go down when I get hasted, I don't see my endurance go down when I get hasted, man why should my damage go down when I am hasted?  It's just wrong.<br>
<br>
Why bother using that spell ever?  to interupt casters?  what the heck is the point.  Most mobs I've ever seen (i have been limited, its true) never _cast_ spells while in melee.  They cast before they get in melee range, they proc while in melee, but it is so g-d rare that I can't even remember any mobs that _cast_ while in melee.<br>
<br>
When I duo with a healer, I have always gotten the attack speed buff.  Fighting yellow, blue, orange mobs the fights don't last all that long and its mostly the opener/poison doing equal or more damage than melee output so why, WHY would this spell be useful?<br>
<br>
Torch <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umironquickblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Miron Quickblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/9/02 3:46:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1627.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.gwi.net/~mboutin/mirhead.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Attack Speed Buff... bad news.</span><hr size=1> Just for a bit of reference endurance use does scale with base weapon delay. I haven't done any tests if weapon damage effects endurance use.<br>
<br>
EDIT: Test results<br>
EDIT: Fixed math to use (style damage / second) and (endurance use / second) rather than style damage and endurance use alone.<br>
<br>
Weapon, DPS, SPD, Max Style Damage, Endurance Use<br>
Falcata 90% qua, 1.8, 2.7, 4, 11.1%<br>
Ferritte Falcata 90% qua, 3.3, 2.7, 4, 11.1%<br>
Ferritte Longsword 90% qua, 3(?), 3.5, 7, 14.3%<br>
Quartz Falcata 90% qua, 4.8, 2.7, 4, 11.1%<br>
Quartz Longsword 96% qua, 5.4, 3.5, 7, 14.3%<br>
<br>
Above is the five weapons I used with a lvl 11 character on lvl 3 monsters. Here are the results in an easier to read manner.<br>
<br>
The 2.7 spd weapons used 11.1% end per swing. Approximately 4.1% / second. They also did approximately 1.5 style damage / second.<br>
<br>
The 3.5 spd weapons used 14.3% end per swing. Approximately 4.1% / second. They also did approximately 2 style damage / second<br>
<br>
The 3.5 spd weapons saw a 33% damage increase for an approximate 0% increase in endurance cost. Even the inexactness of measuring endurance use and the fact that this only takes in account for maximum damage, *not* average damage, 33% is a very large margin of error. Also please note no tests were done using haste or quickness buffs. A few other things to point out. Because of the granularity of the tests 33% is worst case. The 3.5 spd weapons averaged +6 style bonus with a rare +7. Using +6 that gives the 3.5 spd weapons a 13% bonus in damage over the 2.7.<br>
<br>
The moral of the story? The slower the weapon the more damage per endurance. Therefore a weapon with a slower spd will do more damage, with style use, than a quicker weapon. Add that to the apparent lack of dps increase with haste spells and possibly quickness buffs as well and things don't look that great.<br>
<br>
Stupidly I forgot to turn my log on, but I can get this data a second time if desired. If I do it again I will buy more weapons as well. I did this on my lvl 11 who only had so much cash. <p><table width="600" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
